==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acquisitiveness
<hw>Ac*quis"i*tive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality
of being acquisitive; propensity to acquire property; desire of
possession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>The faculty to which the
phrenologists attribute the desire of acquiring and possessing.</def>
<rj><au>Combe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acquisitor</ent>⟦br⟧
